<h3>NI TechComm: Icon database interface</h3>

<p>The Technical Communications department of National Instruments provides on its Intranet site a glossary of icons created for NI software. Unfortunately, the unwieldy structure of the glossary made it difficult to update easily, creating a backlog of icons to be added.</p>

<p>An XML-based solution was developed to simplify maintenance of the glossary, but the backlog itself made manual updates to the XML glossary daunting and tedious.</p>

<p>I volunteered to develop a web-based interface, powered by a MySQL database, that maintained all the components of the glossary. This interface builds the XML glossary, parses the XML into HTML, then publishes the HTML to the Intranet through a synchronization with our configuration management system, Perforce.</p>
