<div class="Column-Left">
<h3>NI TechComm: HTML/FrameMaker conversion tools</h3>

<p>National Instruments documentation is made available through printed manuals, PDFs and compiled HTML help. In recent years, the department has sought out XML solutions to maintain source for these documents efficiently.</p>

<p>I've been involved with a number of projects to transform text between Adobe FrameMaker and HTML.</p>

<p>In one project, I helped to develop a process by which FrameMaker source could be transformed into HTML using only open-source and free tools, such as ImageMagick, GhostScript and PERL. This process was developed as a way to address a limited availablility of FrameMaker licenses.</p>

<p>It's not an easy process -- Maker Interchange Format (MIF) files are transformed to XML, which are then further transformed to HTML. Imported images are extracted from the MIF and converted to PNG.</p>

<p>Another project involved converting source for a compiled HTML Help file into a proprietary XML schema, then creating HTML source from that XML again.</p>

