<h3>NI TechComm: Proprietary XML development</h3>

<p>A number of National Instruments in-house projects involved the creation and maintenace of proprietary XML. I've assisted in some of these efforts, developing tools based on these formats.</p>

<p>One such tool is a content management system which updates a clearinghouse listing of department-specific process documentation. The document listings are stored in a database, and the tool generates HTML pages if updated. It also interacts with Perforce, which manages the source of our intranet web sites.</p>

<p>Two other projects dealt with the maintainence of documents in XML. I assisted with developing PERL scripts and XSL templates to transform these XML documents. These scripts and templates were then incorporated into various nightly build processes among different projects.</p>

